article.headline: Oral Roberts 63, IUPUI 61
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS -- Warren Niles' layup with 1 second to play Saturday night gave Oral Roberts a 63-61 victory over IUPUI. Alex Young's steal and basket tied it with 9 seconds left for IUPUI before Niles won it for the Golden Eagles (4-4, 2-0 Summit). Steven Roundtree and Damen Bell-Holter led Oral Roberts with 13 points, and Niles and Dominique Morrison scored 11. Leroy Nobles scored 21 points to lead the Jaguars (4-5, 1-1). Stephen Thomas had 15 and Christian Siakim 13 for IUPUI. The Jaguars led 50-42 with 9:36 to play before Oral Roberts went on a 10-2 run to tie it on Morrison's shot with 7 minutes to go.
